  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">NIHR - Building Community Cohesion in Kirkuk</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project will bring about significant change to the lives of those in Iraq residing in Kirkuk, providing training on social cohesion and specific vocational skills training followed by small business in-kind start up grants. Kirkuk has been the centre of centuries of conflict between Arabs, Turkmen and Kurdish communities.  The status of the city remains disputed and was not solved in the 2005 Iraqi national constitution.  The context is extremely challenging but without change Kirkuk will remain a fulcrum for violence in the future. Young people remain particularly vulnerable. 
Prior to implementation NIHR will complete a conflict analysis followed by market assessment.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">To build community cohesion through tackling violence and building livelihoods amongst young people in Kirkuk. Peacebuilding training will be provided to 60 young people, followed by skills training to 40 young people, followed by distribution of small business in-kind start-up grants to 20-40 young people.</narrative>
  </description>
